<a name="welcome-to-sgs_bridge" class="anchor" href="#welcome-to-sgs_bridge"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Welcome to sgs_bridge</h1>

<p>This repository will be used to help merge and track ideas, suggestions and general information pertaining to the <a href="http://github.com/erkemp/sgs_bridge">sgs_bridge</a> project.</p>

<h3>
<a name="overview" class="anchor" href="#overview"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Overview</h3>

<p>This project was started in order to create some level of continuity between Steam Group Chats and the <a href="http://reddit.com/r/steamgameswap">r/SGS</a> community.</p>

<p>Chat rooms are a fantastic resource for any community, and access to live/active members should not be restricted to Steam -- or having to keep the chat window the entire time.</p>

<h3>
<a name="main-objectives" class="anchor" href="#main-objectives"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Main Objectives</h3>

<ul>
<li>Provide a <em>near</em>-seamless experience between IRC and Steam Group Chat</li>
</ul><p></p>
